'''Kushitamahimenomikoto Shrine''' (櫛玉比賣命神社, Kushitamahimenomikoto Jinja) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[Matsuyama, Ehime|Matsuyama]], [[Ehime Prefecture]]. It is listed as a {{ill|Shikinai Sho-sha|ja|式内小社|12=draft}} and formerly ranked as a {{ill|Gōsha|ja|郷社|12=draft}}.
The small hill in front of the [[haiden]] (worship hall) is part of an ancient Kofun known as the Kushitamahimenomikoto Shrine Kofun, which spans 75 meters and features a [[zenpokoenfun]] (keyhole-shaped tumulus).
== Overview ==
During the reign of {{ill|Emperor Ōjin|ja|応神天皇|12=draft}}, the shrine was established under an imperial edict, with the local ruler, {{ill|Mononobe Asari-no-Mikoto|ja|物部阿佐理命|12=draft}}, enshrining {{ill|Ame no Hohi|ja|天道日女命|12=draft}} and {{ill|Mikiyanohime-no-Mikoto|ja|御炊屋姫命|12=draft}}.<ref>"Reverently enshrining the deities."</ref>
The shrine is dedicated to {{ill|Amenohohi-no-Mikoto|ja|天道日女命|12=draft}} and {{ill|Mikiyanohime-no-Mikoto|ja|御炊屋姫命|12=draft}}, though some traditions claim the enshrinement of Amenohohi-no-Mikoto alone.<ref>Research on Shikinai Shrines, Volume 1.</ref>
{{ill|Kunitsuhiko Shrine|ja|國津比古命神社|12=draft}} stands opposite this shrine, and both shrines are collectively referred to locally as "Kazahaya-miya Ōujigami" (風早宮大氏神).
== Auxiliary Shrines ==
* **Susanoo Shrine**: Dedicated to {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素戔嗚命|12=draft}}. * **Warei Shrine**: Dedicated to {{ill|Yamanouchi Kōrai|ja|山家公頼|12=draft}}. This shrine is under a separate administration (see {{ill|Warei Shrine|ja|和霊神社|12=draft}}).
== festival ==
The shrine’s annual festival, called "Evening Star" (宵の明星), takes place on the day before the day before [[Sports Day]].
== Related Articles ==
* {{ill|List of Shikinai Shrines in Iyo Province|ja|伊予国の式内社一覧|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kazahaya District, Iyo|ja|風早郡|12=draft}}
